<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is generated during the calibration step "MediaStepSizeDependedError" which is part of media-calibration sequences.
</p></section><section id="GUID-A7817A14-864A-4368-B71F-E0F324A309F0" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Analyse/Repair</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is caused by the fact the M&amp;C-scanner is not able to measure the markers correctly. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Clean the glass of the M&amp;C-scanner and retry the calibration.
</p></section><section id="GUID-6382A921-AB46-4802-A81A-5A46A186AAB6" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Evaluate/Prevention</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">Maintain the engine according to the Care&amp;Use poster.
</p></section><section id="GUID-19EDF35B-4B91-4F44-A758-3CDC47EFAA28" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Background info</b> </title><p class="- topic/p ">This calibration step is used for setting the default media steps in the different print modes. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This error will rarely happen as before this calibration step the M&amp;C-scanner is already checked when measuring the media-thickness.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-12A22F29-4989-4601-A883-7BC951F448D2.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Diagnostics</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
